Tom Cleverley has joined Aston Villa on loan after the Premier League rubber-stamped their last-ditch bid to sign the Manchester United midfielder for the rest of the season.

Villa requested a two-hour extension to get the deal done shortly before Monday's 11pm deadline, and then filed the paperwork 15 minutes after the 1am cut-off point.

However, after considering their case on Tuesday, the Premier League has approved the loan and given the green light for Cleverley to move to Villa Park. 

